label: organic object formed through microbial activity
estuarine biome
SM_comment: The definitions of  marine salt marsh biome and estuarine biome are unsatisfactory in disambiguating these terms to me.  In my opinion, there should be some sort of parent/child relationship between salt-water marsh biome and estuary biome, and then we should include the parent term of these as the pick list item.  I picked estuarian biome as the keeper because marine salt marsh biome has estuary as a synonym in its definition - making me believe that salt water marsh biome could be a subclass of estuarian biome.  This depends on the axis of differentiation perhaps - are we disambiguating marine biomes based on their salt water content, their access to tidal water, their convergence with land-based water sources, their ability to house biodiverse species due to the salt/not salt content.   Not clear.
